fields.value: Exploration of Process-Structure Linkages in Simulated Additive Manufacturing Microstructures

dsDescriptionValue.value: In this data set, we provide microstructure results from the simulation of additive manufacturing processes with the SPPARKS Monte Carlo code. The dataset will be used in our entry to the Materials Science and Engineering Data Challenge. The parameters varied during the study, and their extents are listed in the table below. All simulations were performed on a 300 x 300 x 200 rectangular lattice. All length and timescales are defined within the model and refer to no actual physical system. This release contains the input and output data files, as well as a Python script for the generation of Paraview-compatible files.

fields.value:
The results are organized in a file hierarchy by the input conditions used. An example path to a simulation result is: T5/X/V7-5/W80/D100/L50/HAZ20. The uploaded files have been compressed at the W directory level and labeled as (for example) T5-X-V7-5-W80.tar.gz. The abbreviations used in the file path correspond to:

T -> (T5, T20, T35) The maximum length of the heat-affected-zone tail trailing the melt pool in units of lattice sites. This length can be different (and is typically larger) than the HAZ defined below.

X -> (X, XY) The scan direction used. X = scans only in the +/- X-direction. XY = crossed hatched scans alternating in the X and Y directions with each deposited layer.
V -> (V2-5, V5, V7-5, V10, V15) The scan velocity used in the simulations in units of lattice sites per Monte Carlo step. Dashes represent decimals (e.g. V2-5 = 2.5)
W -> (W60, W70, W80, W90) The width of the melt pool used in the simulations in units of lattice sites.
D -> (D100, D125) The maximum depth of the melt pool in units of percent of layer height  (D100 = 100% of layer height).
L -> (50, 60, 70) The length of the melt pool tail in units of lattice sites. The tail begins at the widest spot of the melt pool (the waist).
HAZ -> (HAZ5, HAZ20, HAZ35) The width of the heat-affected-zone (HAZ) surrounding the melt pool in units of lattice sites. The HAZ is defined at the widest point of the melt pool.

value: The dataset was generated using the SPPARKS Monte Carlo program. Additional information about the program can be found at www.spparks.sandia.gov.
